Aero Services International Incsaid it expects to achieve improvements in overall operationsin the year ending September 30, 1987.    Earlier, Aero reported a 1986 year end net loss of 3.0 mlndlrs compared to a profit of 483,000 dlrs in 1985.    The company said the loss was attributable to costsassociated with its acquisition costs and operating losses ofnine Beckett Aviation fixed base operations purchased in August1985 and discontinued weather service and flight simulatorsegments.    Reuter&#3;